	This is not a complete list, but it is a good start. Many of these items are player-made jewelry. Some are obtained by quests. That should give you a start in being a charismatic bard and bending mobs to your will.
	<br><br>
	<b>Wind Skill</b>
	<br>Since charm uses Wind instruments, it would be a good idea to max your wind skill out each level. Although I haven't noticed any difference in the duration of the charm, supposedly it does increase the magic resistance debuff to the mob. If you're staying a good distance away from the mobs (which you should be), the wind instrument can't hurt. However, I usually wield my weapons and have it on auto-attack, just in case I want to finish one off quickly. Either way, every now and then, hang out in your favorite safe spot, like east commonlands tunnel or your home city and fire up Tarew's Aquatic Ayre(16), Shauri's Sonorous Clouding(19), or Lyssa's Veracious Concord(24) to max out your Wind skill every few levels.


